{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AumExzHVk2SyCCfwNvSFNX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YK1N4RZy31rMwz1YdcSeLe","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/plan.md","content":"# Ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade Change Plan\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-25\n**Cluster:** karma-local-1\n**Current Version:** v1.14.1 (nginx/1.27.1)\n**Target Version:** Next stable release (confirm tag + digest from upstream before execution)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### Controller Deployment (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\n\n**Image:**\nregistry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n\n**Controller args (non-default / noteworthy):**\n- `--watch-ingress-without-class=true` followed immediately by `--watch-ingress-without-class=false`\n  The second flag overrides the first; effective value is `false`. This duplicate/conflicting pair\n  is a defect that must be cleaned up during the upgrade.\n- `--publish-status-address=localhost` — kind-specific; publishes `localhost` as the LB address\n  rather than waiting for a cloud-assigned IP.\n\n**Deployment strategy:**\n- type: RollingUpdate, maxUnavailable: 1, maxSurge: 25%\n- replicas: 1 — with maxUnavailable: 1, the rolling update will briefly leave zero healthy replicas\n- terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0 — intentional; graceful connection drain is handled by the\n  /wait-shutdown preStop hook\n\n**Resources:** requests cpu: 100m, memory: 90Mi (no limits configured)\n\n**Security context:**\n- runAsUser: 101, runAsGroup: 82\n- capabilities: drop ALL, add NET_BIND_SERVICE\n- seccompProfile: RuntimeDefault\n- allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n- readOnlyRootFilesystem: false\n\n### ConfigMap (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\n\nCurrently empty (data: null). No custom nginx tuning is applied; all settings are controller defaults.\n\n### IngressClass\n\nName: nginx, controller: k8s.io/ingress-nginx.\nNot annotated as the cluster-default class (no ingressclass.kubernetes.io/is-default-class annotation).\n\n### ValidatingWebhookConfiguration (ingress-nginx-admission)\n\n- failurePolicy: Fail — Ingress CREATE/UPDATE requests are rejected if the webhook is unreachable.\n- admissionReviewVersions: [v1]\n- caBundle is rotated by the post-install admission patch job; must be refreshed after upgrade.\n\n### Services\n\n- ingress-nginx-controller (LoadBalancer): port 80 -> nodePort 31727, port 443 -> nodePort 32211\n- ingress-nginx-controller-admission (ClusterIP): port 443 (webhook endpoint)\n\n### Demo Namespace\n\n- Deployment demo-app: busybox httpd on port 5678, 1 replica, Ready.\n- No Service or Ingress resource exists for demo-app — the app is NOT currently routed through\n  the ingress controller. E2E traffic testing requires creating those resources separately.\n- curl-test pod: standalone curl utility pod, Running.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\n1. Confirm target version tag and SHA-256 image digest from:\n   https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/releases\n\n2. Kubernetes compatibility: verify the target ingress-nginx version supports k8s v1.35\n   (current cluster version per controller logs: v1.35.0).\n\n3. Snapshot all current manifests before making any changes:\n     kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup-deploy.yaml\n     kubectl -n ingress-nginx get configmap ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup-cm.yaml\n     kubectl get ingressclass nginx -o yaml > backup-ingressclass.yaml\n     kubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission -o yaml > backup-webhook.yaml\n\n4. Review upstream release notes for:\n   - Breaking changes to controller flags between v1.14.1 and target version\n   - Changes to ConfigMap keys (low risk here since ConfigMap is empty)\n   - RBAC or CRD changes requiring separate apply steps\n   - nginx version bump and any directive deprecations\n\n5. Decide on the zero-downtime strategy (see Section 3.3) before scheduling the window.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Configuration Changes Required\n\n### 3.1 Remove Duplicate Conflicting Flag\n\nIssue: the Deployment spec.containers[0].args list currently contains both:\n  --watch-ingress-without-class=true\n  --watch-ingress-without-class=false\n\nThe last value wins (false), but both flags are present — this is a misconfiguration.\n\nAction: during the upgrade manifest update, remove the first (=true) occurrence and keep only:\n  --watch-ingress-without-class=false\n\n### 3.2 Update Controller Image and Version Labels\n\nIn the Deployment, replace:\n  image: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n\nwith:\n  image: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:<TARGET_VERSION>@sha256:<TARGET_DIGEST>\n\nAlso update all app.kubernetes.io/version labels on the Deployment, its pod template, and any\nassociated Service/IngressClass objects to the new version string for consistency.\n\n### 3.3 Address Zero-Downtime Risk (Single Replica)\n\nWith replicas: 1 and maxUnavailable: 1, the rolling update terminates the old pod before the\nnew one is Ready — creating a window with no healthy controller.\n\nTwo options (choose before execution):\n\nOption A — Scale to 2 replicas before upgrade (recommended):\n  Scale the Deployment to 2 replicas, wait for both to be Ready, then apply the new image.\n  The rolling update will drain one pod at a time, always keeping one healthy replica.\n  Scale back to 1 after the rollout completes.\n\nOption B — Accept brief disruption:\n  Proceed with 1 replica and schedule the upgrade in a low-traffic maintenance window.\n  The /wait-shutdown preStop hook drains in-flight connections before the old pod exits,\n  limiting (but not eliminating) connection drops.\n\n### 3.4 Webhook failurePolicy During Upgrade\n\nDuring the pod replacement the admission webhook endpoint (port 8443) will be briefly unreachable.\nWith failurePolicy: Fail, any Ingress CREATE or UPDATE attempted in that window will be rejected.\n\nAction: temporarily set failurePolicy to Ignore before the upgrade, restore to Fail afterward\n(see execution steps below).\n\n### 3.5 Admission Webhook caBundle Refresh\n\nThe post-install admission patch job rotates the TLS cert and updates the caBundle in the\nValidatingWebhookConfiguration. Confirm the patch job is included in the new release manifest\nand that it completes successfully before re-enabling failurePolicy: Fail.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Upgrade Execution Steps\n\nDO NOT EXECUTE until this plan has been reviewed and approved.\nSteps are listed for planning purposes only.\n\nStep 1 — Temporarily relax webhook failure policy:\n  kubectl patch validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission \\\n    --type=json \\\n    -p '[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/webhooks/0/failurePolicy\",\"value\":\"Ignore\"}]'\n\nStep 2 (Option A only) — Scale controller to 2 replicas:\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx scale deploy ingress-nginx-controller --replicas=2\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n\nStep 3 — Apply the updated Deployment manifest (new image + deduped args + updated labels):\n  kubectl apply -f ingress-nginx-controller-<TARGET_VERSION>.yaml\n\nStep 4 — Monitor rollout:\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=5m\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx logs -f deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n  Verify log shows new release version and \"Backend successfully reloaded\".\n\nStep 5 (Option A only) — Scale back to 1 replica:\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx scale deploy ingress-nginx-controller --replicas=1\n\nStep 6 — Run the admission patch job (if provided by new release):\n  kubectl apply -f <admission-patch-job-from-release-bundle>\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx wait --for=condition=complete job/ingress-nginx-admission-patch\n\nStep 7 — Restore webhook failure policy:\n  kubectl patch validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission \\\n    --type=json \\\n    -p '[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/webhooks/0/failurePolicy\",\"value\":\"Fail\"}]'\n\n---\n\n## 5. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\n# Confirm running image matches target\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}'\n\n# Confirm pod is Ready\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/component=controller\n\n# Check logs for reload confirmation and no errors\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=50\n\n# Confirm webhook caBundle is updated (non-empty)\nkubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.webhooks[0].clientConfig.caBundle}' | base64 -d | openssl x509 -noout -dates\n\n# Demo namespace — note: no Service or Ingress exists for demo-app yet.\n# E2E traffic verification through the controller requires creating those resources\n# (separate work item, outside upgrade scope).\nkubectl -n demo get svc,ingress\n\n---\n\n## 6. Rollback Plan\n\nIf the upgrade produces errors, unexpected behaviour, or traffic loss:\n\n  kubectl apply -f backup-deploy.yaml\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=5m\n\nPrevious stable image to restore to:\n  registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n\nAlso restore the webhook configuration if it was patched:\n  kubectl apply -f backup-webhook.yaml\n\n---\n\n## 7. Open Items Before Execution\n\n1. Confirm target version tag and digest (Ops)\n2. Verify K8s v1.35 compatibility with target ingress-nginx version (Ops)\n3. Decide between Option A (scale-to-2) and Option B (accept brief outage) (Team)\n4. Review release notes for flag/ConfigMap renames between v1.14.1 and target (Ops)\n5. Schedule maintenance window if Option B is chosen (Team)\n6. Create demo-app Service and Ingress for E2E traffic testing — separate ticket, not upgrade scope (Dev)\n\n---\n\nPlan generated by automated cluster inspection on 2026-06-25.\nDo not execute until reviewed and approved by the team.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2780,"cache_read_input_tokens":41690,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2780},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"48755629-6b4c-49c1-8c39-4e98c62b8ed0","uuid":"097c63a2-4b4e-4639-8ae9-c8c981779d00","request_id":"req_011CcPzFAR7MhtcSpGeHZPwh"}
