{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0122gKEruqv44vCLtSP5FziV","type":"tool_result","content":"# Ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade Change Plan\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-25\n**Cluster:** karma-local-1\n**Current Version:** v1.14.1 (nginx/1.27.1)\n**Target Version:** Next stable release (confirm tag + digest from upstream before execution)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### Controller Deployment (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\n\n**Image:**\nregistry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n\n**Controller args (non-default / noteworthy):**\n- `--watch-ingress-without-class=true` followed immediately by `--watch-ingress-without-class=false`\n  The second flag overrides the first; effective value is `false`. This duplicate/conflicting pair\n  is a defect that must be cleaned up during the upgrade.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"48755629-6b4c-49c1-8c39-4e98c62b8ed0","uuid":"7541efc8-0384-4e20-bcbd-3e1286e34063","timestamp":"2026-06-25T12:38:32.043Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# Ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade Change Plan\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-25\n**Cluster:** karma-local-1\n**Current Version:** v1.14.1 (nginx/1.27.1)\n**Target Version:** Next stable release (confirm tag + digest from upstream before execution)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### Controller Deployment (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\n\n**Image:**\nregistry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n\n**Controller args (non-default / noteworthy):**\n- `--watch-ingress-without-class=true` followed immediately by `--watch-ingress-without-class=false`\n  The second flag overrides the first; effective value is `false`. This duplicate/conflicting pair\n  is a defect that must be cleaned up during the upgrade.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Axb73mnxQvw3k22voNWPyk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `change-plan` ConfigMap is created in the `demo` namespace with a non-empty `plan.md`. No cluster resources were modified.\n\nHere's what the plan covers, based on what I found during inspection:\n\n**Current state findings:**\n- Controller v1.14.1 with nginx/1.27.1, 1 replica, healthy\n- **Defect:** `--watch-ingress-without-class` is set twice in the args — `true` then `false` (last wins, but the duplicate is a bug to fix during upgrade)\n- `--publish-status-address=localhost` — kind-specific, intentional, must be preserved\n- ConfigMap `ingress-nginx-controller` is **empty** (no custom tuning)\n- No Ingress resources exist in `demo` — the `demo-app` deployment has no Service or Ingress wired to it\n- `ValidatingWebhookConfiguration` has `failurePolicy: Fail` — a risk during the upgrade window\n\n**Plan sections:**\n1. Current state inventory (image digest, args, strategy, webhook, services)\n2. Pre-upgrade checklist (snapshot manifests, check K8s v1.35 compatibility, review release notes)\n3. Three required config changes: deduplicate the conflicting flag, update image + version labels, address the single-replica zero-downtime risk (scale to 2 recommended)\n4. Ordered execution steps with webhook failurePolicy relaxation bookending the rollout\n5. Post-upgrade verification commands\n6. Rollback plan with the exact prior image digest\n7. Open items table for the team to resolve before execution"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":369,"cache_read_input_tokens":54741,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":369},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"48755629-6b4c